  "transcript": {
    "language": "en",
    "is_generated": false,
    "segments": [
      {
        "start": 0.6,
        "duration": 1.6,
        "text": "- [David] Wordsmiths, greetings!"
      },
      {
        "start": 2.2,
        "duration": 3.4,
        "text": "You've found yourself in a\nplace unlike other places,"
      },
      {
        "start": 5.6,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "a place of learning, a place of language,"
      },
      {
        "start": 7.8,
        "duration": 3.5,
        "text": "a place we call the vocabulary zone."
      },
      {
        "start": 11.2,
        "duration": 2.4,
        "text": "Here the unclear becomes clear,"
      },
      {
        "start": 13.7,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "new words become familiar words,"
      },
      {
        "start": 16.1,
        "duration": 2.9,
        "text": "and you become a vocabulary expert."
      },
      {
        "start": 19.0,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "We're gonna look at three words today:"
      },
      {
        "start": 21.1,
        "duration": 3.2,
        "text": "foundation, reinforce, and maximum."
      },
      {
        "start": 24.3,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "I'll define the words,\nwe'll break down the words,"
      },
      {
        "start": 26.4,
        "duration": 1.0,
        "text": "and then at the very end,"
      },
      {
        "start": 27.4,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "we'll use those words in some sentences."
      },
      {
        "start": 29.8,
        "duration": 1.6,
        "text": "Let's begin."
      },
      {
        "start": 31.5,
        "duration": 1.6,
        "text": "Foundation. It's a noun."
      },
      {
        "start": 33.0,
        "duration": 3.1,
        "text": "It means a layer that forms\nthe base of a building"
      },
      {
        "start": 36.2,
        "duration": 1.3,
        "text": "or a structure,"
      },
      {
        "start": 37.5,
        "duration": 3.9,
        "text": "or a factor or idea on\nwhich something is based."
      },
      {
        "start": 41.4,
        "duration": 2.8,
        "text": "So a house sits on a foundation, right?"
      },
      {
        "start": 44.2,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "A slab of rock or stone or concrete."
      },
      {
        "start": 46.4,
        "duration": 1.4,
        "text": "So the house can sit right"
      },
      {
        "start": 47.8,
        "duration": 3.6,
        "text": "and not sink into the Earth,\nas a literal foundation."
      },
      {
        "start": 51.4,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "But to use it in that\nsecond sense, figuratively,"
      },
      {
        "start": 53.5,
        "duration": 3.7,
        "text": "we can say our business rests\non a foundation of trust"
      },
      {
        "start": 57.2,
        "duration": 1.4,
        "text": "or something like that."
      },
      {
        "start": 58.6,
        "duration": 2.9,
        "text": "And as we all know, trust isn't rocks."
      },
      {
        "start": 61.5,
        "duration": 1.4,
        "text": "I'm very smart."
      },
      {
        "start": 62.9,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "Reinforce is a verb,"
      },
      {
        "start": 64.8,
        "duration": 3.0,
        "text": "and it means to strengthen\nsomething by adding to it."
      },
      {
        "start": 67.8,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "To go back to concrete from\nthe foundation example,"
      },
      {
        "start": 70.1,
        "duration": 3.3,
        "text": "lots of concrete buildings\nhave steel rods in them."
      },
      {
        "start": 73.3,
        "duration": 1.3,
        "text": "Maybe you've seen this"
      },
      {
        "start": 74.7,
        "duration": 1.7,
        "text": "when you've walked by a construction site."
      },
      {
        "start": 76.4,
        "duration": 4.3,
        "text": "This is called rebar or a reinforcing bar."
      },
      {
        "start": 80.6,
        "duration": 2.8,
        "text": "You pour the concrete\naround the reinforcing bar"
      },
      {
        "start": 83.4,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "to make the concrete stronger."
      },
      {
        "start": 85.5,
        "duration": 1.2,
        "text": "And finally, maximum."
      },
      {
        "start": 86.7,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "This is both a noun and an adjective,"
      },
      {
        "start": 89.3,
        "duration": 3.9,
        "text": "that means the most or the\nhighest or greatest amount."
      },
      {
        "start": 93.2,
